18:T57b,
      <p>Why do some DTF prints look dull while others pop with neon-like intensity? The secret often lies not in the printer itself, but in the <strong>Color Management System (CMS)</strong> driving it. CADlink Digital Factory 11 sets the gold standard for color fidelity in the DTF industry.</p>

      <h3>High-Fidelity Color Profiles</h3>
      <p>Digital Factory 11 comes pre-loaded with professionally tuned ICC profiles for the most popular DTF printers, inks, and films. These profiles ensure that the red you see on your screen is the red that ends up on the shirt. For advanced users, the integrated <strong>Visual Production Manager</strong> allows for custom profile creation and fine-tuning.</p>

      <h3>Knock-Out Black & Color</h3>
      <p>A game-changer for printing on black or colored garments is the "Knock-Out" feature. The software automatically removes black (or any specific background color) from your design, allowing the shirt's fabric to show through. This not only saves ink but also creates a softer, more breathable print that feels great to wear.</p>

      <h3>White Ink Management</h3>
      <p>Proper white ink generation is crucial for color vibrancy. Digital Factory 11's advanced algorithms automatically generate the perfect white underbase, ensuring colors remain bright and opaque on dark fabrics without making the print feel thick or "bulletproof."</p>
